==English==
[[Image:Monitor LG.jpg|thumb|200px|(3) a monitor]]

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[monitor]]''', '''[[warner]]''', from perfect passive participle '''[[monitus]]''', ''warning'', from verb '''[[monere]]''', ''warn'' or ''threaten''

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-monitor.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# Someone who watches over something.
# A person in charge of something or someone.
# A device similar to a [[television set]] used as to give a graphical display of the output from a [[computer]].
# A class of warship designed for shore bombardment rather than combat with other ships.

